<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-10-0525 </DOCNO><TEXT>A survey is given on design principles of ion source and recoil mass separators.Modern multistage ion source separators are discussed that can achievea low mass cross contamination as well as an element separation withinone isobar. The different types of recoil separators are outlined alsoincluding new time-of-flight separators and filters which eliminate theprimary beam in heavy ion reactions with extreme rejection factors.</TEXT></DOC>